race.comment: The speedy MASTER OF DISGUISE (5) raced well in town before a narrow defeat in Open grade at Albury. Followed with an easy win in an Orange 82, heavily supported again. Will carry just 54kg with the claim and is well placed to keep winning for the in-form local barn. KEIKOKU (7) just missed here this grade 7 days ago over 1200m. Impressed charging home from the back and the longer sprint is sure to suit. Third up now and has solid each-way claims. CHASING A QUID (12) needed the first-up outing and expect him to be much more competitive today. Ran a decent number at Albury before the spell, and carrying just 52kg, he will get every chance to run out the longer sprint. EPAULLO CREED (1) is in the in-form Olive yard and is going well enough to get into the finish. Maps well and the 3kg claim brings him into it. XCEPTIONAL FELLA (13) has weight relief at this level and assess his chances on an impressive win here first-up. Needs a good ride, but he should be around the mark.
